---
description: Keep GroupWire release metadata sourced from the application repository
alwaysApply: true
---

# Canonical public data sources

- `WAGroupManager/package.json` and `WAGroupManager/src/config/changelog.js` are the canonical
  product version and changelog sources.
- `data/releases.json` is generated by the application release workflow. Do not independently
  edit product versions or release notes in this repository.
- Render release history in English only, but preserve the complete generated JSON payload.
- `data/website.json` is the reviewed build-time fallback for public plans, important feature
  highlights, application URL, and legal availability. It must match the public website API
  schema and must never contain the `legacy` plan.
- Hydrate current public data from `https://bo.groupwire.cloud/meta/website`; do not query
  private application routes or expose internal/system administration capabilities.
- All authentication, signup, billing, and in-app links must use the
  `https://bo.groupwire.cloud` origin.
- Keep approval copy limited to a manager review workflow. Do not claim a hard publishing gate
  or an official WhatsApp partnership.
- The version in this repository's `package.json` belongs to the website tooling and is not the
  GroupWire product version.
- Keep this repository deployable as a standalone Render Static Site. Do not add application
  server code, application secrets, or dependencies on the app's runtime filesystem.
